mariadb-10.3 (10.3.0-0+exp1) experimental; urgency=medium

  * New upstream version 10.3.0
  * Remove several patches already merged upstream
  * [MDEV-12516]: Move mysqlbinlog to mariadb-client-* package
  * Rewrite the major.minor specific parts to be generated
    according to the latest changelog entry.  That would help to
    keep the history between MariaDB series (10.3 -> 10.4 ...)
    and to keep the more in the sync in the future.
  * Rename the client libraries libmariadb{3,-dev}
  * Build the client library with GnuTLS
  * Bump the libmariadbd SOVERSION in the package name
  * (EXPERIMENTAL) Use ninja build CMake backend
  * Install various additional files added in MariaDB 10.3
    and enable --fail-missing feature of dh_install
  * Make the mysql_config mariadb_config multi-arch compatible
    by moving the real commands to /usr/lib/$(DEB_HOST_MULTIARCH)
    and putting simple wrappers that call real commands into
    /usr/bin
  * Update debian/copyright with information about added files
    between MariaDB 10.1 and MariaDB 10.3

